美剧中经常出现的“the thing is"是什么意思？


2017-05-31 06:00来源:Echo陪你练口语


原标题：美剧中经常出现的“the thing is"是什么意思？
There are certain phrases that one doesn’t always learn from grammar and English workbooks. Where do you usually learn these phrases? 
1) Talking to real people. 
2) Paying attention to what people say in TV and films. 
3) Reading novels and taking notes of how the author chooses to have the characters speak.
I want to take a quick look at a few.

1. As a matter of fact
You can use this phrase the same way you would use the word “actually”.

As a matter of fact, I do have 5 RMB that you can borrow.
He is here, as a matter of fact.

2. Looking forward to
People say this when they are really excited about something or feel so happy that feel like they can’t wait for that something to happen.

I’m reallylooking forward togoing home and getting some rest after this long business trip.
See you Friday!Looking forward toit!

3. Get along
This refers to people’s quality of relationship or their ability to have a good friendship with someone else.

His wife and his mother-in-lawdon’tgetalong.
He gets alongjust fine with his roommates.

4. For ages
People say this phrase when something takes a long time or when they have been waiting for something to happen for a good amount of time.

The train hasn’t come. We’ve been waiting here for ages.
Wow, it has beenagessince I last saw you! How have you been?

5. The thing is
This phrase is used when someone has a reason for not being able to do something or when they express some difficulty in completing a task.

I want to go home on Friday, but the thing isthat I don’t have enough money to buy a train ticket.
You want me to call her right now? Sorry, the thing isthat I don’t have her phone number saved on my cellphone.

Those are 5 different phrases. So, what can you do to keep these words in your brain? Well, you can practice saying them in sentences. Here is a simple exercise: Say 5 sentences with these words.Go ahead give it a shot! Don’t worry too much about your grammar, just try to use them in a sentence.
1. As a matter of fact
2. Looking forward to
3. Get along
4. For ages
5. The thing is
Thanks for listening today—better yet, don’t just listen, but actually practice saying these sentences!
Until next time…
本期推文主创简介

美化排版 | TingGold
封面图片 | 宇儿
审核校对 | 张津 责任编辑：

